irrxml
------------------------------------------
irrXML is a simple and fast open source xml parser for C++. Why another xml
parser? The strenghts of irrXML are its speed and its simplicity. It ideally
fits into realtime projects which need to read xml data without overhead, like
games. irrXML was originally written as part of the Irrlicht Engine but after
it has become quite mature it now has become a separate project.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.10.0-1
  libgcc1-6.4.0-5
  libirrxml-devel-1.2-1bl1
  libirrxml0-1.2-1bl1
  libstdc++6-6.4.0-5
  pkg-config-0.29.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-10-1
  binutils-2.29-1
  cygport-0.30.1-1
  gcc-core-6.4.0-5
  gcc-g++-6.4.0-5
  libtool-2.4.6-5
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  http://www.ambiera.com/irrxml/

Canonical download:
  mirror://sourceforge/irrlicht/irrxml-1.2.zip

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack irrxml-1.2-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./irrxml-1.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/irrxml-1.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/irrxml-1.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libirrxml0-1.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libirrxml-devel-1.2-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(irrxml)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/irrxml.README
  /usr/share/doc/irrxml/CHANGES.txt
  /usr/share/doc/irrxml/README.txt

(libirrxml0)
  /usr/bin/cygirrxml-0.dll

(libirrxml-devel)
  /usr/include/irrxml/CXMLReaderImpl.h
  /usr/include/irrxml/fast_atof.h
  /usr/include/irrxml/heapsort.h
  /usr/include/irrxml/irrArray.h
  /usr/include/irrxml/irrString.h
  /usr/include/irrxml/irrTypes.h
  /usr/include/irrxml/irrXML.h
  /usr/lib/libirrxml.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/irrxml.pc

